## Engagement Design
- The puzzle answer should be a satisfying security-related word (a tool name, a concept, a term)
- Make it clear in the caption: "No tools needed — solve it from the image"
- Use competitive tension to drive comments (choose 1-2 of these, adapted naturally):
  - "First correct answer in the comments wins bragging rights — let's see who's fastest."
  - "If you solve this in under 5 minutes, your security instincts are already sharper than most."
  - "Tag someone who thinks they know cybersecurity — let's find out."
  - "Last week someone cracked it in 30 seconds. This one's a step harder."
- Do NOT make promises you can't keep ("I'll check your profile" etc.) — readers won't believe them
- Hint should be calibrated so most motivated readers can solve it without Googling
- solution_body should teach the method, not just reveal the answer — "teach a person to fish"
- Close the solution post with: "New challenge every Sunday. Save this series so you don't miss it."
- Tags must include {{ default_tags | join(', ') }} plus 2 relevant topic tags
